<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan People Urged to Inculcate Spirit of Sacrifice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Muhammad
Rafiq Tarar and Chief Executive General Pervez Musharraf expressed
the hope that the people will inculcate in themselves a spirit of
discipline, integration devotion and selfless sacrifice for the
progress and prosperity of the country.
</P>
<P>
In their separate messages on the eve of the Muslim Sacrifice
Festival Eid-ul-Azha which falls on Friday, they said the people
should set aside their personal biases and prejudices to achieve
the aims of reconstruction in accordance with the demands of the
new century.
</P>
<P>
They said the holy day reminds us of the historical event of
matchless obedience, submission and great sacrifice of Ibrahim (a
saint prophet in Quran) and Ismail (son of Ibrahim), who teaches
us moral imperatives, laudable character, determination and
sacrifice.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive in his message said, "We all need more than
ever the spirit of sacrifice, selfless devotion and solidarity to
boost the happiness of the holiday of Eid-ul-Azha."
</P>
<P>
Eid-ul-Azha will be celebrated through out the country on
Friday with religious fervor and enthusiasm.
</P>
<P>
In Islamabad, the biggest Eid congregation will be held at
Faisal Mosque, where President Muhammad Rafiq Tarar, high-
officials and diplomats from Muslim countries will offer Eid
prayers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
