<HEADLINE> Nigeria Leads U.N. Campaign on Stopping Arms Flow in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is leading a campaign of
the United Nations to monitor the flow of conventional arms into
Africa as part of its initiative to rid the continent of
conflicts, the News Agency of Nigeria reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria wants to play a key role in the campaign because it is
also a signatory to the agreement on the importation and
manufacture of small arms of the Economic Community of the West
African States (ECOWAS), the report quoted Nigerian president's
Special Envoy on Conflict Resolution Raph Uwechue as saying in the
country's capital Abuja on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
''It is in everybody's interest to promote peace and stability
instead of pursuing the short-term benefit of selling arms,'' he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
