<HEADLINE> 4 Killed by Torrential Rain in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Severe rain in Kibuye Prefecture
of Rwanda has killed four people and flooding waters took their
bodies, only one body has been recovered, Rwanda News Agency
reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Flooding waters also took over 10 domestic animals including
cows, goats and sheep. Rain has damaged a number of crops, soils
eroded from steep areas down the valley, it said.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rain has hit the western region, where as severe droughts
have been predicted for the north eastern part of the country for
the next three months of March, April and May.
</P>
<P>
The drought predicted is to be caused by the persistent off
shore winds that blow off Rwanda's north eastern region and some
parts of the east, Didace Musoni, director of meteorological
department in the Ministry of Transport and communications said.
</P>
<P>
According to a climate outlook made at the recently concluded
fifth forum of Great Horn of Africa, normal rains are expected in
Rwanda, Burundi, Uganda, north western Kenya, central and eastern
parts of Tanzania but with a likelihood of below average rains in
the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
