<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government on Friday
approved a system that would peg oil export duties to prices on
the world market, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
This system was approved by a government commission on
protective measures in foreign trade and customs tariff policy.
</P>
<P>
The government will issue a directive each time world prices
shift to a new level on a special scale, but the duty cannot
change more often than once every two months, Interfax reported,
quoting Deputy Prime Minister Viktor Khristenko.
</P>
<P>
