<HEADLINE> Athens Olympic Organizers Considers Changing Dates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Athens is considering whether to
bring the 2004 Summer Games forward by two weeks from the planned
dates of August 13-29, organizers said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The proposal came from the International Olympic Committee (IOC)
president Juan Antonio Samaranch, who said the change of dates
would allow professional soccer players to compete at the Games.
</P>
<P>
Athens' chief Olympic organizer Costas Bakouris said that the
IOC wants them to give an answer before the next (IOC) executive
board meeting on April 18-19.
</P>
<P>
The issue could be finalized on May 10-12 when the IOC's
coordination commission will pay its next visit to Athens.
</P>
<P>
The IOC says the date change would allow the top players to
appear for their national teams at the Games by avoiding clashes
with domestic league fixtures or the European Champions League.
</P>
</TEXT>
