<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News Today (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin accepted credentials of five
newly-appointed foreign ambassadors to China at the Great Hall of
the People.
</P>
<P>
The five ambassadors are Juma Rashed Jassim from United Arab
Emirates, Humayun A. Kamal from Bangladesh, David Taylor Irvine
from Australia, Charles Asilia Sanga from Tanzania and Arthur
Alexander Foulkes form Bahamas. The Bahamian ambassador is the
first ambassador from the island country to China.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Vice-Premier Meets British Guest
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen met with Lord William Rees-
Mogg, columnist and former editor-in-chief of the British Times
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Qian expounded on China's basic policy of "peaceful
reunification and one country, two systems" in settling the Taiwan
issue, highlighted president Jiang Zemin's eight-point proposition
in this regard, and said that not allowing the Taiwan issue to
linger on indefinitely is an important part of the Chinese
government's push for reunification.
</P>
<P>
As for the role of the United Nations in the present
international situation, Qian said that despite a dangerous
tendency during the Kosovo crisis of reducing the role of the UN
and its Security Council, and even placing certain nation and
regional organization over the UN, the final settlement of the
crisis within the UN framework shows that the role of the UN in
preventing and settling crisis and disputes, as the world's most
influential and universal inter-governmental organization, is
irreplaceable.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Vice-Premier Meets ROK and Iraqi Visitors
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo met with Namgoong Suek, special
envoy of the president of the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides exchanged views on furthering
the bilateral cooperation in information and telecommunication
fields.
</P>
<P>
Wu also met with Salahyy Gizeer, head of the Commission of
Electricity of Iraq and the two sides exchanged views on expanding
the bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
 CPPCC Vice-Chairman Meets Japanese Guests
</P>
<P>
Chen Jinhua, vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, met here today
with a Japanese delegation of senior journalists.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that members of the delegation had been resident
reporters in Beijing for various Japanese news organizations and
helped a lot in promoting Sino-Japanese friendship and exchange.
</P>
<P>
 Lithuanian FM to Visit China
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Algirdas Saudargas of the Republic of
Lithuania will pay an official visit to China from March 19 to 26,
invited by his Chinese counterpart Tang Jiaxuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
