<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News Today (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua)-- Following are the highlights of
diplomatic news released by Xinhua today:
</P>
<P>
 Sino-Thai Friendship Hailed
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin told visiting Thai Princess Maha
Chakri Sirindhorn that the Chinese and Thai people should pursue
their friendship generation after generation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the two countries are sparing no efforts to advance
an all-round good-neighborly friendship in the new century.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president spoke highly of Sino-Thai relations,
saying that friendship between the two countries is just like that
between two relatives.
</P>
<P>
Since the forging of bilateral diplomatic relations, the
leaders of the two countries have frequently exchanged visits, and
mutual trust and friendship has formed between the peoples of the
two countries, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Sino-Thai friendship has become a model for
relations between countries with different social systems.
</P>
<P>
CASS President Meets With Thai Princess
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, president of the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences
(CASS), met with Thai Princess Maha Chakir Sirindhorn.
</P>
<P>
Li lauded the princess as a good friend of the Chinese people,
and praised her great interest in Chinese culture. The princess
has been learning Chinese for years and has visited many cultural
and historic sites.
</P>
<P>
Ministry of Education Awards Thai Princess
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Education conferred the Language,
Culture and Friendship Award to visiting Thai Princess Maha Chakir
Sirindhorn.
</P>
<P>
At the presentation ceremony in the Great Hall of the People,
Chen Zhili, education minister, said that Sirindhorn is China's
old friend, and beloved by both Chinese and Thailand people.
</P>
</TEXT>
