<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi People Celebrate Eid-ul-Azha Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The holy Eid-ul-Azha, one of the
greatest religious festivals of the Muslims across the world, was
celebrated in Bangladesh Friday with due religious fervor and
traditional gaiety, seeking global peace and universal brotherhood.
</P>
<P>
Dhaka city was festooned with colorful banners and posters
inscribed with "Eid Mubarak (happiness)." Muslims from all walks
of life, dressed in their best finery, offered prayers, visited
houses of friends and relatives, exchanged greetings, distributed
sweets and sacrificed animals among the friends and poor in
celebration of the festival.
</P>
<P>
Important streets and avenues of the capital, road islands and
road junctions were decorated with miniature national flags and
colorful flags inscribed with "Allah-Hu-Akbar (Allah is great)"
and "Eid Mubarak."
</P>
<P>
Eid congregations were held at mosques, parks and open spaces
across the country.
</P>
<P>
President Shahabuddin Ahmed offered Eid prayers at 8 a.m.
Friday, and hosted a reception for the diplomats and
representatives of U.N. bodies and other international
organizations in Dhaka. He exchanged Eid greetings with them.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina was now staying in Saudi Arabia to
perform the holy Hajj. 
</P>
</TEXT>
