<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Canadian Youths Charged With Riot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Montreal court Thursday
charged 10 youths for Wednesday night's riot in a downtown area
against what they called "police brutality".
</P>
<P>
The defendants were among 112 others arrested in the clash with
the riot police, who were called in to restore order after
hundreds of protesting youths began smashing windows and damaging
cars.
</P>
<P>
Municipal court judge Pierre Gaston ordered three of the
defendants to remain in custody until a further decision, while
the other seven were allowed to go home before reappearing in
court at a later date.
</P>
<P>
The protest was organized by a group called Movement Action
Justice, which has said "we won't stop our efforts just because
some tiny groups create havoc."
</P>
<P>
The youths were alleged to protest against the death of a
homeless man in a confrontation with the police at a Montreal cafe.
</P>
</TEXT>
