<HEADLINE> Asprilla Announces Retirement from National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Maverick Colombian striker
Faustino Asprilla has announced his retirement from international
soccer after being left out of the national team for the World Cup
qualifying campaign.
</P>
<P>
Officials said on Thursday that the 30-year-old player had sent
a letter to Colombian Football Federation president Alvaro Fina,
showing his wish to quit from the national side.
</P>
<P>
The player, who plays for Brazilian club Palmeiras, appeared to
be angry at his name absent from the squad for Colombia's opening
World Cup qualifier against Brazil at the end of March. 
