<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shashurin Claims Biatholon World Cup Sprint Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Belarus' Vadim Shashurin put in a
performance free from mistakes to win the men's 10 kilometer
sprint Friday at Khanty-Mansiysk, Russia.
</P>
<P>
Shashurin missed no targets and finished in 26 minutes 28.8
seconds to capture his first biatholon World Cup title since 1997.
</P>
<P>
Devis Da Canal of Italy, the 1997 junior world champion, was 7.
1 seconds behind the winner. He also shot clean and scored his
first career podium finish.
</P>
<P>
Defending overall champion Sven Fisher of Germany made one
penalty loop to finish third, just 9.5 seconds behind the leader.
</P>
<P>
Overall standings leader Raphael Poiree of France came in fifth,
25.1 seconds off the pace. Two penalty loops denied him the
season's World Cup Sprint title, which went to Ole Einar
Bjorndalen of Norway.
</P>
<P>
The race for the overall title is still open as Poiree has 437
points ahead of Bjorndalen, at 417. Bjorndalen finished twelfth
Friday. Fischer stands third with 406 points and two races left.
</P>
<P>
Pursuit finals will be held on Saturday with a mass-start race
ending the season on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Boxer Somboon Retains WBF Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Local hero Somboon Pantasi
outpointed Philippine challenger Roberto Moreno to retain his WBF
junior-bantamweight crown in Roi Et, Thailand on Friday.
</P>
<P>
All three judges ruled in favour of Somboon, who improved his
perfect record to 36 wins after his 31st title defence.
</P>
<P>
The fight was stopped at one point when Moreno badly cut the
Thai boxer above his right eye with an accidental head-but in the
tenth round. But Pantasi floored his opponent twice in the fight
with his fierce right hooks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
