<HEADLINE> Leading Chip Maker Brings World's Fastest PC Chip to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Advanced Micro Devices (AMD), the
world's second largest chip producer, has brought the world's
fastest PC chip to China.
</P>
<P>
The new 1GHz chip, or central processing unit (CPU), makes one
billion calculations per second, much faster than other popular
chips now in use.
</P>
<P>
Leading PC manufacturers including Compaq and Gateway use the
new 1GHz Athlon chip in their latest desktops, which are now
available to customers all over the world via the Internet.
</P>
<P>
However, the chip will not be available in China until the end
of this month, said Thomson Chan, director of marketing for AMD
Asia Pacific.
</P>
<P>
The CPU is the heart of a computer, and its speed plays a
decisive role in the machine's performance.
</P>
<P>
Computer technologies are undergoing unprecedented development,
with more sophisticated models appearing in almost every fields in
growing numbers, said Prof. Chen Zhengqing, president of China
Computer Users' Association.
</P>
<P>
"The new 1GHz chip will have people calculating computer speeds
in giga-bytes rather than mega-bytes," he said.
</P>
<P>
AMD, which has long been challenging the world's top chip maker
Intel through lower prices for its products, has pledged a
consistent pricing strategy since launching the fastest chip ahead
of its competitor, according to Thomson Chan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
