Internal Trade, noted that the contract can be seen as a measure
of domestic commercial firms' challenge to international
competition.
</P>
<P>
Chinese domestic commercial firms will face fierce
international competition when China enters the WTO, he said,
adding that his administration has encouraged domestic commercial
firms to use advanced computer technology to improve their
competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Hualian is an enterprise subordinate to China's largest
retail firm -- the National Hualian Commercial Building Group. It
now has 16 large supermarkets across the country, and by year 2005,
this figure is expected to reach 100.  
