<HEADLINE> Japan Donates Equipment, Polio Vaccine to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government today
donated to China 50 million yuan worth of cooling equipment along
with polio vaccine for 18.5 children at a ceremony held here today.
</P>
<P>
The equipment and polio vaccine, donated under an agreement
China and Japan signed last April, will soon be sent to some areas
that were hit by severe floods in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Health has decided to launch large-
scale immunization against polio this March and April in the
provinces, autonomous regions municipalities of Qinghai, Gansu,
Xinjiang, Sichuan, Chongqing, Tibet, Guizhou, Yunnan, Jiangxi and
Inner Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
In the past decade, the Japanese government has donated 25
million U.S. dollars of vaccine, cooling equipment and other
monitoring equipment for the elimination of polio, and sent over
100 experts to China for technical instruction.  
