<HEADLINE> Norwegian Wins 5-km Classic Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Titleholder Bente Martinsen of
Norway stormed to a victory in a five-kilometer cross-country
classic race on Friday in Santa Caterina, Italy, setting up
another tight finish to the women's World Cup season.
</P>
<P>
Martinsen clocked a winning time of 14 minutes 09.1 seconds,
followed by Russian Olga Danilova in 14:13.3 and Kaisa Varis of
Finland in 14:20.4).
</P>
<P>
The triumph also allowed Martinsen to steal the lead from
Estonia's Kristina Smigun in the standings before Saturday's 10-km
freestyle, the final race of the season.
</P>
<P>
Smigun, who entered the race at the top of the overall
standings, ended up only a disappointing sixth in 14:28.9 on the
tough Santa Caterina course. Martinsen has 1,144 points to Smigun
's 1,125.
</P>
<P>
Martinsen won last year's title by the narrowest possible
margin. She tied with Italy's Stefania Belmondo on 768 points but
captured the title for winning more races over the season.
</P>
</TEXT>
