<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Registered Trademarks Exceed One Million in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The number of valid trademarks in
China has reached nearly 1.1 million, ranking tenth in the world,
according to statistics released today by the Trademark Bureau
under the State Administration for Industry and Commerce (SAIC).
</P>
<P>
Last year, local authorities throughout China handled some 165,
000 trademark applications and approved 122,000, and the latter
figure was 14,700 more than that in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Another 111 new famous trademarks were also confirmed last year,
bringing the total number of such trademarks to 153, according to
the bureau.
</P>
<P>
With the rapid development of China's high-tech industry in
recent years, knowledge and technology has played an increasingly
significant role in the country's economic growth, and more and
more Chinese enterprises have paid growing attention to protecting
their property rights, the trademark right in particular.
</P>
<P>
However, due to loopholes in trademark registration procedure
and supervision, violation of trademark rights and fake products
also take place in the Chinese markets.
</P>
<P>
Bai Dahua, deputy director of the SAIC, said the Trademark
Bureau is stepping up its effort in revising the Trademark Law to
simplify registration procedures and improve supervision mechanism.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local departments for industry and commerce have
joined hands with key enterprises to help them resolve trademark-
related problems, he said.
</P>
<P>
A nationwide computer network is expected to be set up by the
end of this year to supervise trademark registration and improve
management.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
