<HEADLINE> People's Daily Calls for Speeding Up Western Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading newspaper, will publish an editorial tomorrow calling for
accelerating the development of the country's vast western regions.
</P>
<P>
Implementing the strategy of developing the central and western
regions represents a major decision of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) in the new century, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
It will be of great significance for a sustainable growth of
the national economy, the coordinated economic development of all
regions, enhanced unity among all nationalities, and social and
border stability.
</P>
<P>
We must seize this historic opportunity and do a solid job in
carrying out the Party's major decision which will have a far-
reaching impact, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
As an important step in China's reform and opening up and
socialist modernization drive, the strategy of developing the west
is of landmark significance, it notes.
</P>
<P>
Now, conditions and opportunities have matured for implementing
the strategy, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
The past two decades have witnessed the rapid growth of the
eastern regions, which has accumulated much capital, talent,
technology, and management experience.
</P>
<P>
Whiling pursuing further growth, the east is also willing to
support the development of the west, which in turn will offer the
east rich resources and huge market potentials.
</P>
<P>
More importantly, since the establishment of New China over 50
years ago, the country's overall strength has improved markedly,
and now boasts enough economic capability to extend further
support to the west, says the editorial.
</P>
