<HEADLINE> Australian Sharemarket Soars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket
Friday closed less than one percent firmer.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries finished 23.2 points up at 3,203.4.
</P>
<P>
News Corp raced ahead, rising 77.6 cents to 14.32 U.S. dollars
after its recent spate of declines. Other media stocks were mixed,
with Fairfax shedding 6.4 cents to 3.38 U.S. dollars and PBL
slipping eight cents to 8.77.
</P>
<P>
Telcos were generally mixed, with Telstra easing 7.8 cents to 4.
73 U.S. dollars. Cable &AMP; Wireless edged up a cent to 3.79.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector was weaker, with NAB down 27 cents to 12.71
U.S. dollars, Commonwealth easing 30.3 cents to 14.03. ANZ gave up
6.6 cents to 6.55 and Westpac lost six cents to 6.65.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 1.04 billion stocks worth 123.22 million
U.S. dollars, with 825 rises, 809 falls and 488 steady. 
</P>
