<HEADLINE> Fuel Prices Increase in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique has increased fuel
prices by up to 20 percent owing to a rise in imported oil price
and a devaluation of metical against U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Ministry of Mineral Resources and Energy on Thursday announced
rises by 20 percent in the price of diesel and jet fuel.
</P>
<P>
A liter of diesel rose from 5,210 to 6,250 meticais (14,200
meticais to one U.S. dollar at current exchange rate). The
increase for jet fuel was from 3,844 to 4,612.90 meticais a liter.
</P>
<P>
Kerosene went up from 2,780 to 3,330 meticais a liter, which is
a 19.8 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
The price of cooking gas rose by 15.5 percent. A Kilogram of
gas now costs 8,268.3 meticais, instead of the previous 7,157.9
meticais.
</P>
<P>
The smallest increase was for petrol, which went up by 6.1
percent, from 7,580 to 8,040 meticais a liter.
</P>
<P>
These prices are valid for the main ports and surrounding
areas. Inland, the distributors are allowed to add the cost of
transport to the fixed prices.
</P>
<P>
Fuel prices are reviewed every month, and are changed whenever
the import price has risen or fallen by more than three percent
when expressed in meticais.
</P>
<P>
The last fuel price increase was on February 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
