<HEADLINE> Community Clash Kills More in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- More killings and arson were
counted Thursday in the prolonged clashes between the towns of Ife
and Modakeke in southern Nigerian state of Osun, the Post Express
newspaper said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Another newspaper, the Nigerian Tribune, said President
Olusegun Obasanjo is expected to visit the two southern towns and
hold talks with the warring community leaders next week.
</P>
<P>
Major Nigerian newspapers reported Thursday that the clash
which started on March 3 claimed 25 more lives on Wednesday
bringing the death toll to about 75.
</P>
<P>
The two towns are in the heartland of Yoruba, one of Nigeria's
three main ethnic groups, and have a long-standing rivalry over
land ownership and political supremacy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
