<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Govt Hopes IMF Would Not Delay Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government said
Friday it believes the International Monetary Fund (IMF) would not
delay the disbursement of its loan to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
"The amount (of the loan) has also been agreed upon -- as much
as 5 billion U.S. dollars," Coordinating Minister for Economy,
Finance and Industry Kwik Kian Gie told reporters here.
</P>
<P>
He denied that the IMF is planning to postpone the disbursement
of its loan to Indonesia, pending a satisfactory settlement of the
Bank Bali scandal and the bad debts of the Texmaco business group.
</P>
<P>
The Bank Bali scandal, which helped wreck former president B.J.
Habibie's political career last year, revolves around a 60 percent
commission paid by Bank Bali to a firm run by a leading member of
the former ruling Golkar Party for the recovery of 904 billion
rupiah (129 million U.S. dollars) in loans from the Indonesian
Banking Restructuring Agency (IBRA).
</P>
<P>
Texmaco group obtained 754 million U.S. dollars and 1.9
trillion rupiah (270 million U.S. dollars) in loans mostly in pre-
shipment export facilities between November 1997 and February 1998
from the central bank through state banks Bank Negara Indonesia (
BNI) and Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BRI) thanks to intervention from
then president Soeharto. The loans violated the legal lending
limit on BNI as well as the rule requiring prudent management of
the country's foreign exchange reserves.
</P>
<P>
The IMF suspended loans to Indonesia last year over the Bank
Bali scandal, but signed a new agreement in January this year
under which it pledged to disburse the aid package mounting to 5
billion U.S. dollars over the next three years to the country.
</P>
<P>
Kwik Kian Gie said Texmaco's case has been forwarded to the
IBRA.
</P>
<P>
"Texmaco's case does not matter anymore because its (debt)
credit has been transferred to IBRA," he said.
</P>
<P>
Kwik Kian Gie said the selection of a new IMF managing director
to replace Michel Camdessus will not affect the latest agreement
signed by the IMF and Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that the government would bear the burden of the
state budget for the year 2000 if the IMF delays the disbursement
of the loan.
</P>
<P>
The IMF loan is the first source of funds for the state budget.
</P>
<P>
"A delay (in its disbursement) will directly influence some
social projects such as the social safety net program," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0130 </DOCNO>
