<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB To Provide More Financial Aid For Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The financial assistance would be covering 15 projects from
2001 to 2003, aiming to help Sri Lanka reduce poverty and achieve
a sustainable higher level of economic growth by supporting policy
and institutional reforms, human development, basic infrastructure
and environment and natural resources conservation, the release
said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB expressed the confidence that Sri Lanka's economy could
achieve a higher 5 percent growth this year and further 6 percent
in 2001, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka was one of the best aid utilizing countries and
efforts were under way to further increase utilization and
management, the ADB's resident representative John R. Cooney was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The lending level is consistent with Sri Lanka's need for
continued external assistance and based on the satisfactory
portfolio achieved in 1997-1999 in the country, Cooney said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB has provided financial assistance of at least 495
million U.S. dollars to Sri Lanka in 1997-1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
