<HEADLINE> Rwandan Ambassador Urges More Tanzanian Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Rwanda's ambassador to
Tanzania has urged Tanzanian businessmen to boost export to
Rwanda, the Guardian newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with a delegation of Tanzania Chamber of
Commerce, Industry and Agriculture (TCCIA) on Thursday, Zephyr
Mutanguha said while Tanzania provided a major transit facility
for Rwandan imports through Dar es Salaam Port, the country's
business community was failing to exploit the good bilateral ties
and historical relations to boost trade.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda had lots of goods from Kenya and Uganda and almost
nothing from Tanzania, the envoy pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He challenged the TCCIA members, scheduled to leave next Sunday
for Rwanda on a business exploration tour, to exploit the Rwandan
market for Tanzanian goods.
</P>
<P>
He assured the delegation of their safety while in Kigali,
saying that the isolated incidents of killings as reported by
western media in recent days could occur anywhere in the world.
</P>
