<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Azerbaijan Hands Over Iranian Convicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Azerbaijan has handed over a group
of Iranian convicts to the Iranian authorities, the Islamic
Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian consul to Baku, Mojjtaba Vali, told IRNA on Thursday
that 50 Iranians, who had been sentenced to life imprisonment in
Azerbaijan for various convictions, have been repatriated to Iran.
But he did not mention the date of the hand-over.
</P>
<P>
This was the second group of convicts handed over to Iran by
Azerbaijan under an agreement for extradition of prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Azerbaijan released 59 Iranian nationals
found guilty of drug smuggling or illegal entry into the republic
while Iran freed 18 Azeri prisoners sentenced to prison terms in
Iran.
</P>
<P>
Vali said earlier that a total of 120 Iranians had been arrested
in Azerbaijan. However, the fate of the remaining 11 is not clear
so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
