<HEADLINE> Fresh Fighting in Mindanao Kills 47 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Fighting continued Friday in North
Lanao province in the southern Philippine island of Mindanao,
killing at least 41 Muslim rebels and six government troops, the
latest military reports said.
</P>
<P>
The casualty report came after Philippine Armed Forces Chief-of-
Staff Angelo Reyes Friday morning ordered marine soldiers to clear
a town in North Lanao of attacking Muslim rebels.
</P>
<P>
The reports said Reyes deployed more marines in the battle-
gripped Matungao Town in North Lanao where some 400 Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF) guerrillas tried to surround and control
the town hall.
</P>
<P>
"I ordered the marines to clear the town of MILF rebels," said
Reyes who lamented the death of five soldiers and a civilian
military volunteer in the battle.
</P>
<P>
Press reports said the Muslim rebels were holed up in the
mountainous enclaves of the surrounding towns near the boundary of
North Lanao and South Lanao as government troops pounced on them.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Friday, other reports said North Lanao has been
declared a "war zone" as sporadic fighting between government
forces and MILF rebels broke out Thursday.
</P>
<P>
MILF rebels have reportedly attacked six government force
detachments in North Lanao Thursday, killing two army soldiers and
two civilians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
