<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SE Asian Nations Urged to Enhance Market Regulation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
Friday urged the Southeast Asian countries to enhance financial
market regulation in case of a revival of the currency and
economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Manila-based multilateral financial body said it was the
free flow of capital into economies with distorted incentives and
without adequate supervisory or regulatory capacity which led to
the Asian currency and economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
An ADB report recommends policies for preventing recurrence of
the Asian crisis, but it also admitted that since there are no fit-
for-all measures, each country needs its own specific policies in
this front. 
</P>
</TEXT>
