<HEADLINE> Zanzibaris to Elect New President in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Zanzibaris will go to polls
on October 29 to elect the president and members of the House of
Representatives of the isles, the Guardian newspaper reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to a timetable issued Thursday by the Zanzibar
Electoral Commission chairman Zuber Juma Mzee, registration of
eligible voters will begin on August 8 and end on August 21.
Election campaigns will be held between August 22 and October 28.
</P>
<P>
He said nomination of presidential candidates and those vying
for representation in the House should be approved by their
respective political parties by August 19.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not reveal the number of voters expected to
register for this year's elections, nor did he mention how much
money would be used to fund the isles' second multiparty
elections.
</P>
<P>
The first multiparty election in Zanzibar was held in October
1995.
</P>
<P>
No political party has so far announced openly names of
presidential candidates to replace the outgoing President Salmin
Amour whose two five- year terms expire in October.
</P>
<P>
The semi-autonomous Zanzibar region in the Indian Ocean joined
with mainland Tanganyika to form the United Republic of Tanzania
after a revolt in 1964 that ousted the sultan and Omani Arabs who
ruled the island. 
</P>
</TEXT>
