<HEADLINE> Oscar Statuettes Reported Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, March 16 (Xinhua) -- All 54 Oscar statuettes, to
be given to this year's winners during a live broadcast of the
ceremony on March 26, are missing, press reports said late
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences issued a
statement Thursday night, saying the shipment -- from Chicago --
has apparently been stolen from a loading dock in a Los Angeles
suburb.
</P>
<P>
"We figured you'd probably want to know," the statement
concludes. A press conference is scheduled for Friday.
</P>
<P>
Entertainment Tonight, a television newsmagazine, reported that
the statuettes had been delivered by Roadway Express to the Bell
postal service center in California, and the Oscars went missing
from a loading dock there.
</P>
<P>
A new shipment of Oscars is scheduled to arrive on March 24,
two days before the broadcast, in case the originals fail to turn
up, according to ABC network.
</P>
<P>
While the FBI had initially been called in, the matter has now
been turned over to the Los Angeles Police Department Hijacking
Unit.
</P>
<P>
The news comes barely 10 days after ballots to be used in the
selection of the year's best performances disappeared in the same
post office.
</P>
<P>
The red-faced organizers mailed out 4,200 duplicate ballots
after the incident, in which the original shipment was wrongly
diverted into the bulk mail section of the post office.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
