<HEADLINE> Anhui Gears Up Housing Construction In 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province, one of
the nation's economic powerhouses, plans to invest 11.5 billion
yuan on housing construction this year, the same amount as last
year.
</P>
<P>
The amount of floor space to be built this year should reach 18
million sq. m., a slight drop from the 18.2 million sq. m.
finished in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Priority will still go to construction of affordable housing,
then commercial and lower-priced homes.
</P>
<P>
Anhui spent 4.1 billion yuan on its affordable housing
construction in 1999, completing 3.1 million sq. m. of floor space.
</P>
<P>
Living space per capita in the urban areas of the province came
to 9.1 sq. m by the end of 1999. 
</P>
