<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers in N. China Drought-Affected Area Get Adequate Food Supplies, Clothing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 30 million kg of food
and 1.25 million pieces of clothing and quilts have been
distributed to farmers in drought-affected area in north China's
Shanxi province, an official source said today.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Shanxi was hit by its worst drought of the past
century. The drought led to a direct economic lost of 13.3 billion
yuan (1.6 billion US dollars) and left some 7 million people
without enough food and clothing.
</P>
<P>
"We now have enough to eat and wear, the government also lends
us seeds and fertilizer for spring planting," said Li Si'er, a
villager in Shanxi's Luliang region which suffered the most by
last year's dry weather.
</P>
<P>
Li and his fellow villagers harvested almost no grain last year.
</P>
<P>
Since autumn last year, the central and provincial governments
have allocated 113 million yuan for the relief efforts. The
provincial government has also spent six million yuan on
cultivating high-yield and drought-resistant corn seeds in
southern Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
Localities in the province have also organized farmers to work
outside the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Migrant Workers Major Work Force in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The migrant population is nearly one tenth of the total
population in this coastal city. They are mainly employed in the
service trades, building and township businesses.
</P>
<P>
A survey here showed that the transient work force aged between
16 to 50 consisted of surplus farm labors from Hebei, Shandong,
Henan, Anhui, Sichuan and northeast China provinces. The
population of that category topped one million for the first time
last year.
</P>
<P>
Urbanization has created the most job opportunities for migrant
workers, the survey said. A construction worker earns 20 yuan a
day, and a skilled laborer can make up to 40 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Now, housing building and decoration and company security are
among the emerging lucrative markets for migrant workers.
</P>
<P>
With their tolerance for hard and tiring work, and their
willingness to accept comparatively low salaries, migrant workers
have secured a large part of the job availabilities in the service
sector.
</P>
<P>
The survey estimated that migrant workers spent 2.3 billion
yuan of their earnings in the city annually, which is based on an
average monthly consumption of 180 yuan per person.
</P>
<P>
However, the migrant workforce is also responsible for 35
percent of the crimes in Tianjin for the past three years. To curb
this, the municipal government has worked to improve personnel
management and training of migrant workers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Consumer Market Enjoys Fast Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China's consumer market saw
speedier growth in the first two months of this year with sales
volume of consumer goods hitting 576.78 billion yuan (about 70
billion U.S.dollars), surging 10.9 percent year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
The National Bureau of Statistics said today that the growth
rate of sales volume between January and February was three
percentage points higher than that of the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Sales volume in January stood at 296.29 billion yuan, climbing
11.3 percent on an annual basis, and that of February amounted to
280.49 billion, up 10.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The catering industry has maintained its strong growth momentum
in the past two months, with business volume jumping 19.5 percent
to 60.51 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
During that period, sales of consumer goods in urban areas
enjoyed a faster growth than in regions at or below county level,
the bureau reported.
</P>
<P>
Analysts from the bureau attributed the booming consumer market
to the spending spree brought about by festivals and holidays in
the first two months, mainly the New Year's Day and the Spring
Festival, as well as the state's policy of stimulating domestic
demand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Shows Signs of Thriving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR) of China has shown thriving scenes since the
establishment of the SAR government and will have a promising
future, a senior legislator in Macao said.
</P>
<P>
The fine scenes can be seen in the aspects of improved public
security, economic resurgence and booming tourism, according to
Tong Chi Kin, a senior member of the Macao Legislative Council and
spokesman for the Executive Council of the Macao SAR government.
</P>
<P>
Tong made the remarks in a recent meeting with a group of
people from the Hong Kong SAR of China.
</P>
<P>
He said that after the establishment of the Macao SAR
government, the situation of public security has been greatly
improved and the number of criminal cases has dropped obviously.
Over the past three months, local residents can feel that public
security has turned for the better.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the morale of the police is raised under the
SAR government rather than the Portuguese rule. They have become
more efficient in cracking criminal cases.
</P>
<P>
As long as the police make more efforts, they will surely be
able to live up to the expectations of local residents and
tourists, Tong Chi Kin said.
</P>
<P>
The economy has also shown signs of recovering. More business
opportunities have come, internal consumption market tends to be
booming, export maintains steady growth and unemployment rate
begins to go down.
</P>
<P>
The legislator noted that recently two companies from Hong Kong
have moved their headquarters to Macao, one pharmaceutical factory
will be put into production soon, and a foreign bank is going to
open a branch in the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the SAR government is improving its
administrative efficiency to offer investors better services, Tong
Chi Kin said.
</P>
<P>
With regard to tourism, the number of tourists in the first
month of the year increased about 20 percent over that in the same
month of last year.
</P>
<P>
What's more important, Tong said, Macao's unique cultural
features are attracting more tourists in addition to the
traditional gambling business.
</P>
<P>
As the income from tourism is an important part of government
revenue in Macao, the SAR government will try to make more people
around the world acquire more favorable knowledge about Macao.
</P>
<P>
Now the government has set up tourism offices in 14 big cities
all over the world, and more shall be set up to better promote
Macao's tourism, Tong Chi Kin said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
