<HEADLINE> Allen Iverson Suspended for Missing Practice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Allen Iverson was suspended by
Philadelphia 76ers for at least one game for missing the team's
shootaround Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
Iverson, who led the NBA scoring standings, was sidelined in
76ers' loss to the Miami Heat Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
"I felt I had a better relationship with this organization,"
Iverson said with angry after the game. "I don't think this is
fair at all."
</P>
