<HEADLINE> Private Firm to Set Up University Town in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A private enterprise in east
China's Zhejiang province will spend 800 million yuan (963,000 U.S.
dollars) to build a university town in the Changping District of
suburban Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Jili Group signed a letter of intent with Beijing Foreign
Studies University and Beijing Broadcasting Institute to jointly
run universities in the special zone.
</P>
<P>
Building of the initial phase of Jili University Town will be
completed by the end of August and will cover 350,000 sq.
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Included in the start-up phase will be seven colleges enrolling
a total 2,000 students this year. Graduate and foreign students
will be enrolled during the second phase.
</P>
<P>
Education experts say that a university town is a win-win
concept, as businesses can provide money and logistic service for
universities while universities can concentrate on teaching and
educational administration. 
</P>
