<HEADLINE> Beijing's First Hospital for Wild Animals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's first hospital for
protecting and treating wild wildlife has opened for business
recently.
</P>
<P>
About 10 veterinarians are employed at the hospital, on the
city's north side, which was established with the approval of the
relevant Beijing municipal departments.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 wild animals have been rescued and treated at the
hospital since it opened on a trial basis a year ago. Some of the
injured wild animals were first rescued by local residents and
then taken to the hospital for medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
Domestic pets are also cared for at the hospital, which is
affiliated with the Wild Animals Protection Center under the
Beijing Forestry Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Income from the hospital is used to protect and rescue wild
animals.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese capital has nearly 50 veterinary clinics. 
</P>
