MANILA, March 17 (Xinhua) - North Lanao province in the
southern Philippine island of Mindanao is declared Friday a "war
zone" as sporadic fighting between government forces and Moro
Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) rebels broke out Thursday, the
military report said.
</P>
<P>
The military accused the MILF of breach of the on-going peace
negotiations between the MILF and the government in Mindanao.
</P>
