<HEADLINE> China, Malaysia Finalize WTO Technical-level Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China and Malaysia finalized
their technical-level negotiations on China's entry to the World
Trade Organization (WTO) Thursday, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Trade officials of the two countries held the technical-level
negotiations on China's entry to the WTO Wednesday and Thursday,
said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian side will submit the results of the negotiations
to its government for approval, after which the two sides will
officially sign the agreement. 
</P>
