<HEADLINE> Indonesian President's Aide Meets Aceh Separatist Movement Military Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Abdurrahman
Wahid's close aide Bondan Gunawan held a talks with Abdullah Syafi
'ie,the military commander of the separatist movement in Aceh at
an undisclosed place in the province on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During a 20-minute unprecedented talks, Gunawan, state
secretary and government control secretary, presented Wahid's
message to leaders of the Free Aceh Movement (GAM), an underground
movement in the province which had been launching a fighting
against the central government over the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
The two officials later admitted that they now have the basis
to create a long-waited reconciliation between the two sides,
according to the Indonesian Observer Friday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first encounter ever between representatives of the
government and GAM.
</P>
<P>
Wahid's expressed readiness earlier to hold negotiations with
GAM leaders, including Hasan Tiro, has been positively welcomed by
GAM secretary general Tengku Don Zulfahri.
</P>
<P>
"Our readiness to negotiate with the Indonesian government is
not because we are surrendering to the Indonesian Armed Forces (
TNI) but to comply with demands of the Aceh people," Zulfahri said.
</P>
<P>
The reason behind GAM's readiness to hold talks with the
government is to heed the wishes of the people of Aceh for a
political solution to the Aceh question, he was quoted by the
Indonesian Observer as saying.
</P>
<P>
Violence in Aceh has intensified recently and since the year
began more than 200 people have been killed in clashes between GAM
guerrillas and the government forces. But the situation is getting
better now.
</P>
<P>
"Well, its getting better because the general situation is now
very good," the president said here Wednesday when asked about the
strife-torn province.
</P>
<P>
"Go ask the people of Aceh themselves. They all know that GAM
is loosing position, that's why in several areas, GAM attack
schools and other public places hoping the people will suspect TNI,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
The president urged TNI soldiers and police not to retaliate
against these attacks, but to remain in their barracks "unless
going to pray at the mosque". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0270 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Troops Capture Nine Ethic Albanian Extremists in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Troops Wednesday seized a
large quantity of weapons and ammunition, and arrested nine men
during a raid on an ethnic Albanian extremist hideout in north
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The Tanjug News Agency quoted a U.S. military spokesman as
saying on Thursday that  helicopters and armored vehicles were
used in the search. Soldiers clashed with extremists in five areas,
he said, but without giving details.
</P>
<P>
Observers believe the U.S. Army took this action out of concern
for the progressive upgrading of violence committed by ethnic
Albanian militants. 
</P>
