<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Children Killed in Central Quebec Traffic Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Seven pre-school age children were
killed in a traffic accident Thursday in Central Quebec, according
to Quebec police.
</P>
<P>
The children were on a day-care outing to a sugar shack when
their mini-van collided with another vehicle near St. Jean
Baptiste deNicolet between Montreal and Quebec City.
</P>
<P>
Four were killed on the spot while three others died at the
hospital. Three other children were injured with one still in
critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Provincial police spokesman Daniel Lamirande said the mini-van
jumped over a guard rail on a secondary road. "Most of the
children were thrown out of the van on impact. It was a pretty
horrible scene," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Hysterical parents rushed to the scene of the accident and saw
their children lying in the field, said Lamirande.
</P>
<P>
An investigation is underway to identify the cause of the
accident. The road was reportedly wet and the driver of the
children's mini-van appeared to have lost control before the mini-
van crashed through the guard rail and was struck by the other
vehicle, the police spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien, Quebec Premier Lucien
Bouchard and the Quebec legislature offered their condolences to
the victims' parents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
