<HEADLINE> CAF to Grant Credit to Ecuador, Colombia, Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Andean Development Corporation
(CAF) will grant 922 million U.S. dollars in loans to Ecuador,
Colombia and Venezuela, said the organization's representative
Freddy Rojas here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The CAF backed a future 3-year credit of 700 million dollars
for Ecuador in order to reactivate the country's economy and
strengthen its banking system.
</P>
<P>
National Council for the Modernization of the State (Conam)
chairman Ricardo Noboa said that the Interamerican Development
Bank (IDB) is willing to help the Popular Capitalization Program
of Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
However, Noboa said there is concern in the IDB about
Ecuadorian administrative problems that had impaired the delivery
of a 30 million dollars credit to modernize the transportation
system.
</P>
<P>
The IDB also pointed out that there were conflicts among the
Public Works Ministry, the Executive Corporation for the
Reconstruction of the Zones Affected by the El Nino phenomenon (
Corpecuador), and some provincial prefectures on the distribution
of the credit, which must be defined before the money reaches
Ecuador, said Noboa. 
</P>
