<HEADLINE> Sampras, Lapentti, Arazi Through to Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras rallied from one
set down to defeat Byron Black of Zimbabwe 4-6, 6-3, 6-2 and earn
himself a berth in the quarter-finals of the Tennis Masters Series
tournament in Indian Wells, California on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Sampras, who won the Indian Wells tournament in
1994 and 1995, struggled in the first set against Black, who has
no victory record in their previous four matchups. He was hitting
volleys either into the net or out, including three in a row at
one point.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Sampras found his touch at the net and also
mixed in hard groundstrokes that landed just inside the line.
</P>
<P>
By the third set, he was in complete command, and finished off
the match with a 196-kph ace.
</P>
<P>
In Thursday's other action, eighth seed Nicolas Lapentti of
Ecuador topped Frenchman Nicolas Escude 3-6, 6-4, 7-6 (7-3) and
unseeded Hicham Arazi from Morocco downed Max Mirnyi of Belarus, a
qualifier, 7-5, 3-6, 6-4
</P>
<P>
Arazi, who shocked world No. 1 Agassi 6-3, 3-6, 6-3 in the
first round, set up a clash with Lapentti in the quarterfinals.
</P>
</TEXT>
