<HEADLINE> Anhui Introduces New "Space" Vegetables  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The agricultural sector in east
China's Anhui Province has introduced new varieties of "space"
vegetable seeds to replace traditional ones.
</P>
<P>
The seeds were sent into space for two weeks for special
breeding, and the use of these seeds developed after exposure to
strong radiation in space has the advantages of being disease
resistant and high yielding.
</P>
<P>
Local agronomists note that the so-called "space tomato, red
pepper, and cucumber" are growing well at a number of farming
centers in the province.
</P>
<P>
These vegetables are expected to be grown widely throughout the
province's rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
