<HEADLINE> Seminar to Lure Foreign Investors in Telecom Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China's potential in
telecommunications is to be reassessed at a seminar scheduled for
later this month in Beijing, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
With focus on the country's entry into the World Trade
Organization (WTO), the seminar -- Roundtable on Convergence in
China -- is set for March 27 and 28. The seminar is expected to
attract foreign investors for the telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
The event is co-organized by the State Economic and Trade
Commission and the Economist Conferences and is a division of the
London-based Economist Group. The seminar coincides with new
discussion between China and the European Union on China's WTO
entry.
</P>
<P>
European Trade Commissioner Pascal Lamy will be in Beijing for
China WTO entry talks starting on March 27.
</P>
<P>
The Economist Conferences have organized major discussions
several times between Chinese governments, industry officials and
senior corporate executives.
</P>
<P>
China had spent 20 billion US Dollars annually on
telecommunications infrastructure over the past five years.
</P>
</TEXT>
