<HEADLINE> Peru's Exports Up Over 15 Percent in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Peru's exports in February grew more
than 15 percent over the same period of 1999, General Manager of
Exports Promotion Commission Antonio Castillo said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Garments, wood and agricultural productions took the lion's
share of non-traditional exports, while those traditional exports
of copper, gold, fishmeal, and coffee still increased by a large
margin, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his confidence that the United States would
grant the extension of the Andean Tariff Preferences Law to Peru,
especially for textile products.
</P>
<P>
The exports of textiles and garments this year will reach 500
million U.S. dollars, and those to the U.S. could increase 40
percent with the help of favorably tariffs, he said. 
</P>
