<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, March 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton said Thursday that he
will tell Indian and Pakistani leaders during his stay in South
Asia that their nuclear arms race could only bring in a "dangerous
future."
</P>
<P>
"India and Pakistan have legitimate security concerns. But I
will make clear our view that a nuclear future is a dangerous
future for them and for the world," Clinton said in videotaped
remarks to the Carnegie Nonproliferation Conference in Washington.
(US-India-Pakistan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian police rounded up three Hamas militants
with a lot of explosives in a West Bank village Thursday on the
eve of the scheduled renewal of Israeli-Palestinian peace talks in
Washington .
</P>
<P>
The Hamas men surrendered to the police after they were
surrounded at Qallil, near the town of Nablus, said a Palestinian
security officer who spoke on condition of anonymity. (Palestine-
Hamas-Arrest)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States said Thursday that it was not
aware of imminent resumption of peace talks between Syria and
Israel.
</P>
<P>
