</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Twenty-five persons have been killed since Tuesday
night in the recrudesced community clash between the towns of Ife
and Modakeke in Nigeria's southern Osun State, the official news
agency said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), the death toll
during the clash starting March 3 between the two Yoruba
communities has amounted to 75. (Nigeria-Clash)
</P>
<P>
