</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Greek Defense Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos said
Thursday that what was necessary was the undertaking of
initiatives for peace in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo, with the
inflow of investments and the reconsideration of the embargo
against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
