<HEADLINE> Gronholm Leads in Portuguese Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Marcus Gronholm of Finland clocked
3 minutes, 6.2 seconds in a 3.2-kilometer special stage to lift
his Peugeot 206 to the first place in the opening section of the
four-day Portuguese Rally in Baltar, northern Portugal on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Gronholm's compatriot Harri Rovanpera inspired his Toyota
Corolla to second place by finishing just 0.2 seconds behind.
Colin McRae, last year's winner in a Ford Focus, took the third
with 0.4 seconds off the lead.
</P>
<P>
Featuring the fourth competition in the world championship
circuit, the Portuguese Rally will go into full gear Friday with
the 158.8-kilometer first leg, which starts in Fafe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
