<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0294 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway Beat China to Enter Algarve Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGARVE, Portugal, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Norway upset World Cup
runners-up China 3-0 in their last group B match to enter the
Algarve Cup women's soccer tournament here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Norway, who won group B after the victory, will face World Cup
champions United States in the final slated for Saturday in Loule.
</P>
<P>
Dagny Mellegren scored all three goals, including a double in
the first half. At least two goals came from her taking advantage
of the loopholes in the Chinese defence.
</P>
<P>
A typical example came after China trailed Norway 1-0 in the
first half. After a clumsy effort for a Chinese full-back to head
the ball back to the goalkeeper, Mellegren raced forward to blast
the ball into the net.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Ma Yuanan said although China and Norway are
about the same level, China was not prepared psychologically
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He added that his team would draw a lesson from this loss when
they prepare for this summer's Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Mia Hamm scored the only goal when eventual group A winners
United States defeated Sweden.
</P>
<P>
In other third-round actions Thursday, Denmark beat Portugal 2-
0 in group A, while Canada defeated Finland 2-1 in group B.
</P>
<P>
China will now vie for third place against Sweden, while
Denmark and Canada will battle for fifth place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
