<DOCNO> XIE20000317.0297 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian Foundation Gives Loans to Poor Chinese Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Yiping, a migrant worker
in the southern boomtown of Guangzhou who was fired for being
pregnant, would have given up the fight for her job if not for
financial support from the Guangdong Women's Federation (GWF).
</P>
<P>
The charity organization has received 500,000 yuan of loans
from the Asian Federation since International Women's Day on March
8, to be used to help poor women fight for their legal rights in
Guangzhou and Shenzhen, the two fast-developing cities in south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to pay legal fees for women involved in
lawsuits, and Zhang Yiping was one of the 50 women using the money
to protect their legitimate rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
This is the Asian Foundation's first time to finance this type
of project in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
