<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Steel Giant Pledges to Fulfill Contracts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Baoshan Iron and Steel
Company in Shanghai, one of China's leading steel complexes,
announced Wednesday that the fire that broke out in its first iron-
making system on February 28 would not affect its ability to
fulfill contracts.
</P>
<P>
The company pledged that their clients' interests will be
guaranteed, all contracts will be carried out on time and goods
delivered as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
Since the fire, Baoshan has upgraded its systems which produce
hot-rolled and cold-rolled steel, steel tubes and high-speed steel.
</P>
<P>
To date, the company has fulfilled 5,160 contracts, 130 of
which are for exports. And 53,000 tons of steel products ordered
by clients for export have been delivered as due.
</P>
<P>
Converters that were damaged in the fire are expected to resume
production at the end of this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
