<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers in Hainan Keen on Technological Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 2.1 million farmers in
south China's Hainan Province have attended technological training
courses and earned certificates of achievement over the past two
years.
</P>
<P>
The province began to initiate the farmer-training project in
its cities and counties in 1998, and now more than 600
professionals have given lessons in the fields of agriculture,
animal husbandry, aquatic production, farm economy, and breeding
and cultivation.
</P>
<P>
A local agricultural official said that farmers on the island
have used their newly-learned techniques to improve agricultural
production. About 40 percent of the province's agricultural output
value is due to the application of the techniques.
</P>
<P>
With up-to-date agro-technology training, the official said,
more than three million farmers in the province will master
advanced technological farming skills in the next three years.
</P>
