<HEADLINE> South China City Cares For Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- People over the age of 70 in
Guilin, a tourist mecca in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, now
can ride public buses in the city for free.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, retired officials and disabled soldiers enjoy the
same preferential treatment.
</P>
<P>
The no-cost rides are part of the city' social welfare project
launched in 1998, which provided free bus rides for the elderly in
some parts of urban area.
</P>
<P>
More than 20,000 people have taken advantage of the offer.
</P>
<P>
A local official said that in the coming year, senior citizens
will have the same opportunity when traveling to counties and
townships around the city.  
</P>
