<HEADLINE> Arsenal Beats Werder Bremen in UEFA Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer club
Arsenal were by far the better side as they secured a two-goal
advantage to take into the away leg of their UEFA Cup tie with
Werder Bremen Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
A goal in each half for Thierry Henry and Freddie Ljungberg
were the difference between the sides, although the Germans may
consider themselves lucky the margin was not much bigger.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal established a silky rhythm from the outset that saw
them trouble the German defense with shots from Henry, Patrick
Vieira and Gilles Grimandi inside the first 15 minutes.
</P>
<P>
By contrast, Werder Bremen never once looked like scoring but
will still go into next week's second leg with some confidence
after overcoming a 1-0 deficit in the last round to knock-out
holders Parma 3-2 on aggregate. 
