<HEADLINE> Tyson Set for May Showdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- World controversial boxer Mike
Tyson will fight in Milan on May 20, although his opponent has yet
to be confirmed.
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for the Italian promoters confirmed the fight,
which had initially been scheduled for April 8, would now take
place at a later date, but made no comment on whether Tyson would
fight Lou Savarese, the American mentioned in media reports as his
likely opponent, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman said details of the bout would be announced at
a media conference in Milan on Friday at 1100 GMT.
</P>
<P>
Tyson's managers have been trying to negotiate more European
fights since he demolished British champion Julius Francis in
Manchester in January.
</P>
<P>
The former world heavyweight champion boxer has a big fan base
in Europe and his Manchester fight was sold out in two days,
despite a row over him being allowed to box in Britain. 
