<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Phillips Agrees Five-year Deal with Sunderland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Kevin Phillips has agreed a new
contract with Sunderland to make him the highest-paid player in
the club's history and one of the biggest earners in the
Premiership.
</P>
<P>
The five-year deal replaces the player's current contract,
which expires in 2002.
</P>
<P>
Sunderland manager Peter Reid told the club's website: "Kevin
is the leading goalscorer in the Premiership and an England
international.
</P>
<P>
"It's a long time since we have had that at the club so I'm
understandably very pleased."
</P>
<P>
Phillips has hit 85 goals for the club since arriving from
Watford for 650,000 pounds in the summer of 1997.
</P>
<P>
He has scored 25 Premiership goals this season - eight more
than his nearest rival - with 10 games still remaining.
</P>
<P>
Phillips is the fifth first team regular at Sunderland to
commit himself to a new deal in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Sorensen, Gavin McCann, Chris Makin and Alex Rae have
already agreed new contracts.
</P>
<P>
Rae has signed on until 2003 while highly-rated youngster
McCann has signed until 2005.
</P>
<P>
"Gavin has proved himself to be a top quality midfield player
and will be as good as new after his injury," said Reid.
</P>
<P>
"Alex is playing very well at the moment. Everyone understands
the problems he has had to face and he has fought them well.
</P>
<P>
"He is now playing some of his best football since joining the
club," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
