</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- More than 1.7 million Saudi and foreign pilgrims
on Friday continued their pilgrimage, or Hajj rituals by starting
symbolic "stoning of the devil" in Mina, ritual site in the holy
city of Mecca in Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
The stoning ritual will last for three days and each pilgrim
will throw seven pebbles at each of the three different pillars
symbolizing the devil as a sign of the human being overcoming the
devil.
</P>
<P>
After this rite pilgrims will return to the Grand Mosque in
Mecca to complete the last part of their Hajj journey by performing
circumvention around the holy Kaaba, which according to Koran is
the oldest house of worship in the world. (Saudi-Pilgrimage)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A scheduled Israeli troop withdrawal from south
Lebanon will be complete and Israel will not retain any part of a
border zone in Lebanon after the pullout, Regional Cooperation
Minister Shimon Peres said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Peres made the remarks to visiting British journalist Patrick
Seale, biographer of Syrian President Hafez al-Assad. During their
meeting, Seale asked if Israel would, as reported in Israeli media,
keep parts of the border zone it occupied in southern Lebanon as
part of a unilateral withdrawal plan. (Israel-Lebanon)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
