<HEADLINE> Presidents Of 54th, 55th Sessions of GA to Preside Over Millennium Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations General
Assembly(GA) had decided that the presidents of its fifty-fourth
and fifty-fifth sessions would jointly preside over the Millennium
Summit, U.N. sources said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The General Assembly made the decision amid the unique symbolic
moment of the Summit, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Millennium Summit of the General Assembly will be held from
6 to 8 September in New York under the overall theme "The role of
the United Nations in the Twenty-first Century."
</P>
<P>
The three-day Millennium Summit of the United Nations is
expected to be the largest-ever gathering of heads of State or
government.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations General Assembly designated its fifty-fifth
session, starting on September 5, as the Millennium Assembly, and
decided to hold the Summit in order to consider how the United
Nations can best meet the challenges of the new century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
