<HEADLINE> Toronto Stocks Hit New High at 9706.34 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Canada's benchmark Toronto Stock
Exchange 300 composite Index hit a new high at 9,706.34 at noon
EST Friday, up 218.30 points, or 2.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
This handily topped the previous intraday high of 9,662.06 and
was well above the record close of 9,580.87 on March 6.
</P>
<P>
A total of 113.5 million shares were traded as of midday at the
value of 2.96 billion Canadian dollars (about 2.01 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the overall market, advancing issues outpaced decliners 600
to 401, while another 251 remained flat.
</P>
<P>
Market behemoths Nortel Networks and BCE Inc. again powered the
TSE index advance, with Nortel stock climbing 13 Canadian dollars
(about 8.83 U.S. dollars) to 188.10 (about 127.70 U.S. dollars)
and BCE Inc. up 10.75 Canadian dollars (about 7.30 U.S. dollars)
to 179.25 (about 121.69 U.S. dollars) a share.
</P>
<P>
The tech-led gains on the Toronto Stock Exchange have been in
upward trend for the past few months, breaking the 8,000 mark in
mid-December last year, pushing through 9,000 in early February
and aiming at the magic 10,000 level already surpassed by the Dow
Jones industrial average. 
</P>
