<HEADLINE> Brazil To Make Easier Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This was announced Friday by BCB adjunct director Antonio
Carlos Martins at a symposium held at the American Chamber of
Commerce to discuss the new system.
</P>
<P>
Martins said that nowadays the time needed for the registration
of foreign capital has been too much because of its volume.
</P>
<P>
BCB data show that foreign investment went from 900 million U.S.
dollars in 1994, to 32 billion dollars in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The BCB said that the new registration system, called
Electronic Declaratory Registry, can be made in the Internet,
substituting for the paper documents now required, and will give
more transparency to the access of the investments.
</P>
<P>
BCB sources said that the new system will reduce from one to
two years, to only 30 minutes the time needed to register the
entrance of foreign capital to the country.  
</P>
