<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed With Dow falling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Friday with the Dow Jones industrial average falling on profit-
taking while other indicators rising.
</P>
<P>
At the close of session, the Dow index fell 35.37 at 10,595.23,
trimming its big gain of 819.36 points in the previous two days.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index rose 4.54 at 1,463.01 and the technology heavy Nasdaq
composite index rose 80.74 at 4,798.13.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index fell as investors cashed out of selective
industrial stocks in the wake of their strong rebounding on
Thursday and Wednesday. In the previous two days, the blue chip
stocks recovered 42 percent of their losses in the past two months.
</P>
<P>
Among the stocks leading the Dow lower today were Alcoa,
International Paper and General Motors.
</P>
<P>
Technology stocks were higher on both the Nasdaq and the New
York Stock Exchange. Applied Materials, Sun Microsystems and 3Com
rose on the Nasdaq while Nortel Networks and America Online also
moved higher on the NYSE.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.54 at 574.78,
according to preliminary calculations.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 8-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,591 down, 1,430 up and 467
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 1.29 billion shares from 1.48 billion
in the previous session. 
</P>
