<HEADLINE> Europe's Main Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (Xinhua) - London's stock market ended a see-
saw session virtually unchanged Friday as weakness in drug, oil
and bank stocks muted the upward momentum provided by Vodfone
AirTouch and Telewest.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index closed up 0.8 point at 6558.0, as investors
breathed a sigh of relief at US consumer price data indicating
inflation had remained under control in February.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark index was up about 10 points, or 0.1 percent, for
the week.
</P>
<P>
The pan-European FTSE Eurotop 300 closed up half a percentage
point at 1698.66, led by gains of 3 percent each in its computer
and information technology sectors and a 2.57 percent jump in the
telecom segment.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Xetra Dax closed substantially more than one percent
higher but off its intraday highs after a volatile session ahead
of a triple witching options and futures expiry in New York.
</P>
<P>
The Index of 30 bluchips closed 126.96 or 1.67 percent stronger
at 7710.92 points. The index lost 265.03 points from March 10.
</P>
<P>
Shares in Paris closed narrowly higher, inspired at the open by
a surge in US markets and supported by strong gains in index
heavyweight France Telecom.
</P>
<P>
The CAC-40 bluechip index closed up 45.75 points or 0.73
percent at 6304.28 points. The index closed down 206 points on the
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
