<HEADLINE> Britain Welcomes German Lifting Beef Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (Xinhua) - The British Government Friday
applauded Germany's decision to lift a ban imposed on imports of
British beef after outbreaks of mad cow disease.
</P>
<P>
The ban was imposed in 1996 after scientists believed mad cow
disease, or BSE, could spread via infected meat from cattle to
people.
</P>
<P>
The UK's agriculture ministry Nick Brown said it was now up to
the authorities and meat industry representatives to regain
consumer confidence abroad.
</P>
<P>
"I really do hope it has a knock-on effect. France is now
completely isolated on this issue within the EU ...They really
should think again ... they're defying the law, " he said.
</P>
<P>
The National Farmers Union also welcomed the decision (NFU). "
This was the right decision and leaves France conspicuously out on
a limb in Europe over its illegal ban," NFU President Ben Gill
said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
British beef could be back on sale in Germany by early April.
</P>
</TEXT>
